RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORDY G hustled leaving the break and assumed command in the early going, set a pressured pace into the turn, carved out fast fractions while pressed to the quarter marker, shook free into the stretch and drew clear heading to the furlong marker, felt mild late pressure from the runner-up and kept to task in deep stretch to prevail. ONE BIG SMILE broke alertly, took back off of the solid early pace and tracked three wide into the turn, raced close up to the pace three wide heading to the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch, re-rallied in the late stages, could not reel in the winner in deep stretch and held safely in the end for second. R HEART OF GOLD chased the solid early pace, went two wide into the turn, angled four wide into upper stretch, rallied in the final sixteenth and got up in the final strides to secure third. ZEE CARROT EAGLE tracked the early pace from a three wide position, shifted to the two path into the turn and gained ground at the quarter marker, chased FORDY G to mid-stretch, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outfinished for third. THECHIEFHASTRICKS chased three wide along the turn and offered a mild late rally. WOLF'S LIFE lacked early speed, saved ground into the stretch and did not factor. BIG IRISH asked for speed in the early stages, pressed the solid pace from the inside and kept pressure on FORDY G to the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE CALABRESE KID sent leaving the break and assumed command into the first turn, was engaged by POUR ON THE COLE into the backstretch run and set a prompted pace to the half-mile marker, carved out moderate fractions while pressured to the quarter marker, drifted to the two path into upper stretch, met the bid of ATTENZIONE to mid-stretch, lost the lead to that rival at the furlong marker, battled with ATTENZIONE while drifting into the final sixteenth, determinedly came again in deep stretch and outfinished the runner-up in the final strides to prevail. ATTENZIONE rated nicely off of the early pace and saved ground into the first turn, tracked the moderate pace through the backstretch run and saved all of the ground heading to the far turn, mounted an inside bid nearing the quarter marker and vied for the lead into upper stretch, battled with THE CALABRESE KID to mid-stretch and took a narrow lead at the furlong marker, dueled into the final sixteenth and held a slim lead in deep stretch, was outfinished by the determined winner in the final strides and held clearly for second. GALLANT WARREN settled in the second flight early on, advanced into the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace outside of rivals, was well placed four wide into the far turn, maintained that four wide path into the stretch, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch and was outkicked, while holding safely at the finish for third. LORD WIMBORNE (IRE) allowed to settle, saved ground into the first turn then was guided to the three path into the backstretch run, tracked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, inched closer while two wide along the far turn and continued his gain into the stretch, could not sustain his bid into the final sixteenth and flattened in deep stretch. BROKEN FINGER away in good order and was prominent in the early stages, shifted three wide into the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace to the half-mile pole, bid three wide approaching the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch and gave way. POUR ON THE COLE asked for early speed and stalked the pace three wide into the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and prompted the moderate pace to the half-mile pole, continued to pressure the pacesetter into the far turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSY CITY stumbled at the start then was content to track behind the moderate pace set by AUTISM INCLUSION, stayed towards the inside then got stuck behind horse on the far turn, had to check while full of run between the five-sixteenths and quarter poles, still had to wait for room turning into the stretch, got loose, surged ahead and won clear. DIAMOND CONCERTO last away, bided time near the rear of the pack, made steady forward progress down the backstretch while racing three wide, continued to race out in the clear through the turn, attempted to keep CLASSY CITY from getting out at the top of the stretch then could not match strides with that foe in the final furlong. UNCLE LEON showed some good speed from the break but was keen and hard to place going into the clubhouse turn, went to press AUTISM INCLUSION on the lead while the rider kept a measured half length or so behind that rival, then was set down at the quarter pole, took over the lead at the top of the stretch ran on well but was unable to hold off the top two but finished well clear of the next horse. AUTISM INCLUSION was able to secure the lead without being asked, then had to deal with UNCLE LEON stalking just off the flank but not pressing the issue, was allowed to set fairly moderate fractions to the far turn, gave way at the quarter pole when that foe mounted a serious challenge at the quarter pole and had nothing to offer in the stretch. CORAL CAT was outrun into the first turn then took up a tracking position behind the two leaders, held the rail to the far turn, was unable to quicken with the rest passing the three furlong marker and chased the rest of the field to the finish.

IMPACT ZONE forwardly placed leaving the start and tracked three wide into the first turn, rated into the backstretch and tracked the moderate pace from the second flight, was roused into the far turn and mounted a three then four wide bid nearing the quarter marker, vied for the lead into upper stretch, met the bid of RICH GOLD and battled with that rival to the furlong marker, dueled to the sixteenth-marker, could not match strides with the winner into deep stretch and was well clear of the rest for second. SKY DINSKI was forwardly placed leaving the start and tracked the pace into the first turn, shifted to the three path into the backstretch and stalked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, was coaxed along three wide and between runners into the far turn and gained ground at the quarter marker, was asked for more into the stretch and chased the top two to the furlong grounds, could not impact the top pair in the final stages and held for third at the finish. BALLROOM PRINCE was allowed to settle and raced two wide into the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and tracked four wide to the half-mile marker, shifted to the two path heading into the far turn and gained ground approaching the quarter pole, was floated five wide nearing the top of the lane, recovered and shifted to the three path into upper stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch and just missed for third. HICKORY WIND settled along the inside to begin, tracked the moderate pace through the backstretch run and was well placed approaching the far turn, gained ground nearing the quarter marker then came in tight heading into upper stretch, was boxed in to the furlong marker, found room into deep stretch and did not offer a late response. MEDAL ICE was prominent away from the start and raced close up to the early pace, advanced into the backstretch run and contested the decent pace outside of SGT POWELL heading to the half-mile marker, disputed the pace two wide into the far turn, could not keep pace into upper stretch and tired in the lane. SGT POWELL away in good order and was hustled to establish the early lead, showed the way along the first turn then was engaged by MEDAL ICE and contested decent fractions with that rival to the half-mile marker, disputed the pace into the second turn, was overtaken in upper stretch and gave way in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY BUCKET LIST settled well off the pace mid-pack down the backstretch, was set down and put into a drive from the three furlong pole, swung five wide into the stretch, was full of run at the furlong grounds, took command into deep stretch and drew clear in the final stages. AS LUCK HAPPENS was quick away from the break and sent to the front, then allowed to set an uncontested lead through reasonable fractions took on and repelled a challenge from MAVERICK ROSE approaching the quarter pole, opened up in the stretch then could not hold off the late bid of MY BUCKET LIST while finishing well clear of the next horse. CARDINAL TRICK veered in and bumped WESTERN SIERRA at the start, then raced six wide down the backstretch, made some forward progress through the turn while under a drive, came into the stretch four wide then shifted out a path for clear run, produced a mild rally while lugging in and managed to gain the show. STOUT outrun early, the was ridden to regain contact with the field while saving ground through the turn, kept on under strong handling and was gaining some late but was never a serious threat. I AM AMADEO was forced into the gap after the break when FIINCAIRN came over sharply, then rushed up into contention and was inside of the group chasing AS LUCK HAPPENS through the early fractions, lost position into the stretch and gave way. VRONSKY FEINT away in good order, conceded the early lead and stalked ALFONSIA into the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and prompted the decent pace to the half-mile marker, pressed ALFONSIA into the far turn and took command into the stretch, was set down at the furlong marker and held foes at bay to the sixteenth-pole, was overtaken in deep stretch by MY YAMMY LADY, was outfinished by the top two in the final strides and held clearly for third in a good effort. SHEZARUNAWAY allowed to settle and raced two wide and between runners into the first turn, tracked the decent pace through the backstretch run and improved position heading to the half-mile pole, raced two wide into the far turn and continued a steady gain to the quarter marker, maintained a two wide path into the stretch and continued her advance at the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch but was gaining in the final stages. STREET SHADOW forwardly placed away from the start, settled in the second flight and saved ground along the first turn, was well placed while tracking the decent pace from the inside approaching the half-mile marker, saved ground into the far turn and raced within aim heading to the quarter pole, angled three then four wide into the stretch and improved position at the furlong grounds, could not sustain that run into the final sixteenth and weakened. CAROLE LOMBARD prominent leaving the start and tracked the early pace four wide into the first turn, tracked the decent pace through the backstretch run while outside of runners, maintained that four wide path into the far turn and raced within aim at the quarter pole, lost position into the stretch and got caught in a bit of traffic at the furlong grounds, offered a mild late rally in the final sixteenth but needed more. BID ON THE PRIZE steadied after the break to avoid INCREDIBLE SHOT, then immediately angled to the rail, saved all the ground to the stretch, had to wait for room passing the three-sixteenths pole, got clear and responded to intermittent urging to gain second while no match for the winner. J D'S RUDE BOY was not pushed for speed from the gate and held back to avoid getting caught very wide on the first turn, was still caught three to four wide, then made steady forward progress down the backstretch, started a rally on the far turn but was still last at the quarter pole, went eight wide turning into the stretch and responded to strong handling to gain third.
